The paper deals with designing models for machine learning tasks defined on sets, which is a problem that is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science. The paper proposes a deep network architecture that can operate on sets and can be deployed on a variety of scenarios including both unsupervised and supervised learning tasks. This makes it likely that the paper belongs to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), and computational linguistics (cs.CL).
